description:
"Kennedy" is a news panel show hosted by Kennedy Montgomery. Kennedy Montgomery is a libertarian that you may recognize from 90's MTV, Stossel, and the Independents.

_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2

Kennedy kicks the night off talking polls. Donald Trump & Hillary Clinton are still in the lead. Ben Carson is nipping at Donald Trumps heels. Carely has dipped 4 points. Rand Paul is DOA.

Hillary and Trump are still at the top. What do they have in common? Our party panel consists of ANDY LEVY, CHARLES COOKE, and JIMMY FAILLA. They've got a few ideas. Jim Webb drops out of the race despite a decent showing on the Democratic debates. Martin o'Malley appears on the view to play guitar poorly and sing even worse. George W. Bush rips Ted Cruz.

Jennifer Lawrence recently sparked off a discussion about the wage gap between women and men. Rhonda Rousey didn't seem to completely agree. Hadley Heath Manning of the Independent Women's Forum is here via satellite to give her opinion.

The panel returns to talk Star Wars hysteria. Kennedy bought 8 tickets. Study shows that men are afraid of smart women. 

JILLIAN MICHAEL's is in studio to talk about her new Spike TV show "Sweat Inc." She talks exercise, her show, big fitness crazes.

Nightcap: Hollywood & the 2016 election.
